		    <title outputclass="H4H3xx" class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">501.171-1</ph> GSA orders and handbooks.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d16e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li otherprops="abc" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d15e18" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						             Heads of contracting activities (HCA’s) may issue internal agency guidance, as described in FAR 1.301(a)(2), in the form of a GSA order or handbook.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li otherprops="abc" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d15e27" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						             GSA orders and handbooks must not unnecessarily repeat, paraphrase, or otherwise restate the FAR, GSAR, or GSAM.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li otherprops="abc" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d15e36" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						             The handbook, Writing GSA Internal Directives (OAD P 1832.3B), prescribes policies and procedures for issuing GSA orders and handbooks.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
